-- LME Nickel and Aluminum Trading Jumped in June
-- B y   A g n i e s z k a   T r o s z k i e w i c z
-- 2013-07-11T09:44:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-11/lme-nickel-and-aluminum-trading-jumped-in-june-table-.html
Buying and selling of nickel futures
and options rose 38 percent from a year earlier in June on the
London Metal Exchange. Trading increased 37 percent for aluminum
and 30 percent for copper.  Following are monthly futures and options trading volumes
for selected metals on the LME. The exchange said July 2 first-half trading climbed 9 percent to 86.78 million lots, with
nickel and cobalt leading growth.  To contact the reporter on this story:
